Being a cold Canadian, I know great HOT soup. Try putting in a julienne of snow pea and red pepper last minute for color and snap!

Rating: 3
A beautiful soup. I briefly sauteed the shrimp shells with a little chopped garlic and a few shallots before adding the water, which brought out the flavor nicely. Taking a cue from Memphis, also added a chopped chipotle in adobo (better than the powder) to the strained broth for a little more depth and kick.

Rating: 4
I have been making this soup for years. It is very easy as long as you can get all the ingredients. I have made it for company and they have asked for the recipe. I never get tired of this soup...and it will remain in my recipe file forever!

