I'm not sure what I did wrong--I followed the instructions and everything, but the end result was just vile-smelling and tasted salty and fishy. I ordinarily have pretty good luck with Epicurious recipes, and I love Thai and other Asian foods. Maybe it was just a fluke, but I doubt I'd try it again.

Rating: 4
This is a great soup, which is easy to make. It goes better, I think, served over rice. I substituted powdered chipotle which gives a more complex flavor than a Thai or serrano chili.

Rating: 3
Excellent. Very authentic and light soup. You can also make this with vegetables instead of shrimp. Impressive, but relatively easy to make.